{"TopicId":187338,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Hype Train Thread","CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T20:46:45Z","PageNum":7,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"runner78","CreatedById":168980,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-16T20:03:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223671881\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568435583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lu K.\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/14/2019 at 6:33 AM, Lu K. said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYa they should have picked Unreal Engine, that way modders can use blueprints \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCorrect me if I\u0027m wrong, but so far i know, Blueprints are quite slow.... I don\u0027t now you can convert Bluprints to C\u002B\u002B also for Mods, but\u00A0then you need compile it\u00A0separately for each Platform (Windows, Linux, MacOS)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223671885\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568436911\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/14/2019 at 6:55 AM, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause it\u0027s cheap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nOn the UI video posted above... No. Just no. Can we \u003Cem\u003Eplease\u003C/em\u003E stop with the ultra-low-contrast shades-of-grey pancake-flat UI trend already?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP1 navball: Looks mostly like a real-life navball, obvious effort put into 3-dimensional representation of 3-dimensional object.\u003Cbr\u003E\nKSP2 navball: Somebody made a circle in MS paint, did a colour-fill with pastel tones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook at pictures of modern cockpits, real navballs are also flat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Commander Zoom","CreatedById":8333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-18T18:32:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd \u003Ca href=\u0022https://xkcd.com/2204/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Exkcd\u003C/a\u003E boards the Hype Train, full speed ahead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-18T19:36:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568831572\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00228333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Commander Zoom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Commander Zoom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd \u003Ca href=\u0022https://xkcd.com/2204/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Exkcd\u003C/a\u003E boards the Hype Train, full speed ahead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp_2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022149.32\u0022 height=\u0022439\u0022 width=\u0022294\u0022 src=\u0022https://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/ksp_2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-18T19:53:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223671895\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568440618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/14/2019 at 1:56 AM, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my world, a released product has a release-worthy UI to go with it - not placeholders, not mockups, not a quick and-dirty 4-colour overlay on the screen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP2 has been released?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMan that was quick, last I heard (this morning) is it wasn\u0027t even in beta yet\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-18T20:36:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223671895\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568440618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/14/2019 at 1:56 AM, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my world, a released product has a release-worthy UI to go with it - not placeholders, not mockups, not a quick and-dirty 4-colour overlay on the screen.\u003Cbr\u003E\nReleased == core systems fully functional, ready to play, no big upheaval for a while. The UI that lets you \u003Cem\u003Einteract\u003C/em\u003E with the game is a pretty important thing to get right early-on IMO.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuite true, and I totally agree.\u00A0 So what is your problem with a pre-alpha view of a UI which is not release-worthy, not fully polished, etc?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-18T23:21:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674104\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568838961\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuite true, and I totally agree.\u00A0 So what is your problem with a pre-alpha view of a UI which is not release-worthy, not fully polished, etc?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a fair number of people who seem to believe ShadowZone\u0027s 5-minute photoshop job is going to be the final UI.\u00A0 I\u0027m not entirely sure why...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T01:08:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568848911\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a fair number of people who seem to believe ShadowZone\u0027s 5-minute photoshop job is going to be the final UI.\u00A0 I\u0027m not entirely sure why...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause it\u0027s on the INTERNET.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T04:59:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673137\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568664192\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168980\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022runner78\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/17/2019 at 8:03 AM, runner78 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook at pictures of modern cockpits, real navballs are also flat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue. Assuming it\u0027s a modern cockpit, navballs are digital FPDs. My argument isn\u0027t whether or not it\u0027s round though, it\u0027s whether or not it\u0027s supposed to look like real cockpit instrumentation with all the 3D greebles and knobs that implies.\u003Cbr\u003E\nEven cuting-edge aircraft have physical instruments, for a real-world cockpit that looks like the UI preview we\u0027ve seen, you\u0027re talking VR goggles and nothing else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568836387\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP2 has been released?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMan that was quick, last I heard (this morning) is it wasn\u0027t even in beta yet\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. See the comment I was responding to, regarding finishing the UI after release.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674104\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568838961\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuite true, and I totally agree.\u00A0 So what is your problem with a pre-alpha view of a UI which is not release-worthy, not fully polished, etc?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing, the unpolished placeholder-nature of the UI is fine... It\u0027s the style I don\u0027t like.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMy comments about a released product needing a release-worthy UI were in response to:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223671893\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568439364\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/14/2019 at 5:36 PM, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t want to make the same mistake KSP1 did and put a ton of work into the UI before they release the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot the video itself.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568848911\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbelieve ShadowZone\u0027s 5-minute photoshop job is going to be the final UI.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot at all. I mean the video is titled \u0022secrets of the KSP2 user interface\u0022, so I\u0027d expect it it at least hint at the style and layout of the final product, but it\u0027s clearly still in early-development.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAgain: State: Fine. Style: Yuck.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-19T05:10:03Z\u0022 title=\u002209/19/2019 05:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 19, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T06:13:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA new thread is in order: \u0022Is Star Theory currently working on the next KSP 3 game?\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"runner78","CreatedById":168980,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T06:45:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568848911\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a fair number of people who seem to believe ShadowZone\u0027s 5-minute photoshop job is going to be the final UI.\u00A0 I\u0027m not entirely sure why...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I saw the video, I immediately thought, that will now go around as a new KSP UI...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568869188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue. Assuming it\u0027s a modern cockpit, navballs are digital FPDs. My argument isn\u0027t whether or not it\u0027s round though, it\u0027s whether or not it\u0027s supposed to look like real cockpit instrumentation with all the 3D greebles and knobs that implies.\u003Cbr\u003E\nEven cuting-edge aircraft have physical instruments, for a real-world cockpit that looks like the UI preview we\u0027ve seen, you\u0027re talking VR goggles and nothing else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpaceX crew Dragon has no physical instruments, not even physical controls, only touch screen monitors.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd for Airplanes, as newer the model, the less\u00A0physical instruments.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T08:01:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674364\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568875520\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168980\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022runner78\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, runner78 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpaceX crew Dragon has no physical instruments, not even physical controls, only touch screen monitors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool. Where are those touchscreens in the \u0022secrets of the KSP2 user interface\u0022 video again?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far as I recall, the Dragon still has a physical joystick and physical buttons for critical functions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Davi SDF","CreatedById":197335,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T08:04:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674349\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568873587\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA new thread is in order: \u0022Is Star Theory currently working on the next KSP 3 game?\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP3: you can build a death star, a Dyson Sphere, create real space wars, and all this in real life.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T13:30:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568869188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot at all. I mean the video is titled \u0022secrets of the KSP2 user interface\u0022, so I\u0027d expect it it at least hint at the style and layout of the final product, but it\u0027s clearly still in early-development.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAgain: State: Fine. Style: Yuck.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that\u0027s where you have the problem: The video is about the *layout,* but not the *style.*\u00A0 Judging the style from that video is like judging how a person looks from their 3-year old\u0027s picture of them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Commander Zoom","CreatedById":8333,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-20T04:50:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen videos where the Blizzard devs discuss the process of developing new zones.\u00A0 The proto-maps of those zones are basically whiteboard diagrams and flow-charts, only slightly prettied up, and that tiny bit of polish is only (I\u0027d guess) because they\u0027re made with shape drawing tools, not sketched by hand with pen or stylus.\u00A0 They are not at all representative - except in the loosest, most conceptual sense - of the finished design.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes Star Theory need to slap \u0022Pre-Alpha\u0022 on \u003Cem\u003Eeverything\u003C/em\u003E they release?\u00A0 Would it actually help, or would people continue to jump to conclusions and/or speculate wildly based on the thinnest of \u0022evidence\u0022?\u00A0 (My money is on the latter.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-20T04:53:56Z\u0022 title=\u002209/20/2019 04:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 20, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Commander Zoom\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-20T16:25:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EStar Theory hasn\u0027t even released an image of the UI officially.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 People are getting up in arms about a YouTuber\u0027s diagram to help explain what he saw in an interview.\u00A0 They can\u0027t even slap pre-alpha on it because \u003Cem\u003Eit\u0027s not theirs.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"csiler2","CreatedById":62800,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-20T20:12:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568869188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/18/2019 at 11:59 PM, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing, the unpolished placeholder-nature of the UI is fine... It\u0027s the style I don\u0027t like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo you don\u0027t like the style of something that\u0027s a non-development team member\u0027s quick and dirty representation of a temporary placeholder?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou are really stretching for something to gripe about. I\u0027m going to hold my complaints on UI until I actually see something that the dev team has officially released as their art direction for the UI. Maybe you should too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MunaExplorer","CreatedById":200396,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-21T13:56:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg data-ratio=\u002259.67\u0022 width=\u0022300\u0022 alt=\u0022EKaalqx.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/EKaalqx.png\u0022\u003EMy Ticket\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-23T06:28:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674364\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568875520\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168980\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022runner78\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/19/2019 at 1:45 AM, runner78 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpaceX crew Dragon has no physical instruments, not even physical controls, only touch screen monitors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWrong.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.spacex.com/sites/spacex/files/images/dragon/interior_3.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKnobs and membrane buttons.\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.spacex.com/sites/spacex/files/images/dragon/interior_4.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAnother view\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.spacex.com/sites/spacex/files/images/dragon/interior_6.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAnd another\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"runner78","CreatedById":168980,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-23T06:43:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yes, NASA required that, i think the original design was without. I don\u0027t now, if this controls\u00A0used in normal operations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-23T07:05:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223676180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221569221025\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168980\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022runner78\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, runner78 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yes, NASA required that, i think the original design was without. I don\u0027t now, if this controls\u00A0used in normal operations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe original design had a few buttons and a joystick. They got rid of the joystick for some reason.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-23T12:25:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPTKNP aka Federation aka Oryol had started from that joystick.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThey just realized that will never do such wonderful handle, and cancelled it to keep their face.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/53IdflEZQ5k?start=224\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Schtiebuu","CreatedById":161552,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-25T20:18:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny idea where i can \u0022buy\u0022 an group ticket \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraston","CreatedById":188565,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-29T16:02:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*Male voice, in 3 different octaves*\u00A0All aboard the KSP2 hype train! Tickets are free, as long as you take em\u2019 early enough! Please do not push and shove to get into the train, you\u2019ll clog the aisles!\u201D *Female voice, slightly\u00A0bitcrushed*\u00A0And NO FILTHY NA-err-UNCULTURED SPACE GAME HATERS! You can\u2019t board unless you present your ticket and your motive! *original tri-octave speaker* \u201CShould you\u00A0have any complaints, train staff shall promptly place you inside of one of the many \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003ESRB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u2019s placed at the back of the train. You may experience small amounts of uncomfortable vibrating, but remember... complaints shall be answered with immediate\u00A0annihilation.\u201D *both* \u201CHave a happy and safe ride, tickets after destination shall cost 60 dollars.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-29T16:02:29Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2019 04:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Fraston\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-30T00:07:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Georgia, serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP 2 POEM:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003EYeah, KSP.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003EBurn down my PC...\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-30T01:18:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ve been running at a pleasant 0.075c for the past few weeks, after an initial burst of acceleration from the announcements. I\u0027ve adjusted the reverser to use steam a little more efficiently. I expect the hype to increase over the next few months, we should break the light speed barrier in early 2020, I expect.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPassengers are encouraged to share videos discussing KSP2 or showcasing footage here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}